<c74object name='dk.datatranspose' category='' module='dataknot'>
    <digest>Transpose and modify descriptor streams
</digest>
    <description>The <o>dk.datatranspose</o> object takes incoming descriptor data (of any kind) and &#39;transposes&#39; it in different ways. The input can be lists or <o>buffer~</o> s and the same will be output.
</description>
    <discussion>Since this is a somewhat abstract idea, I&#39;ve done my best to apply what is perceptually meaningful (where possible) changes to the descriptors as they are transposed. This is different for each descriptor type, and is more effective in some than others. On the normal descriptors (i.e. <o>dk.descriptors~</o>) and melbands the results are perceptual and quite effective. With MFCCs, given their abstract nature, this is less the case.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, FluCoMa Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

    <!-- INLETS -->
    <inletlist>
        <inlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor and control in
</digest>
            <description>Incoming descriptors as a list or <o>buffer~</o> as well as control input.
</description>
        </inlet>
    </inletlist>
    <!-- INLETS -->

    <!-- OUTLETS -->
    <outletlist>
        <outlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor output
</digest>
            <description>Transformed descriptor output.
</description>
        </outlet>
    </outletlist>
    <!-- OUTLETS -->

